; A function the type system happily accepts and the termination checker
; refuses to bless: the recursion never descends, so no structural argument
; exists. The kernel labels it `termination unproven` rather than rejecting
; it — and when its oath runs, the fuel bound converts the infinite loop
; into an honest FALSIFIED verdict instead of a hang.

(defn spin [] [(x Int)] Int
  (spin x)
  (prop claims-zero [(x Int)]
    (== (spin x) 0)))
